So was the work of the person of Cali who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A Dactyloscope from Cali has passed on to history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano'.
The work of these officials is crucial.
Last November 4 a Dactyloscope of the CIT of Cali passed on to history as the person who confirmed the identity of the Supreme Chief of the Farc: "Alfonso Cano", confronting his fingerprints.
Seven Dactyloscopes working in the local ITC offices this week were the "availability" tour of Elias González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working for 21 years in the field of judicial research.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipalities of Chocó, where he often had to spend more than five days in the forest to reach the place where the bodies were to be identified.
In 2000, he moved to the capital of Valle, and after taking appropriate courses, he specialized in dactyloscope, which is the study of friction skin, i.e. sweats and feet.
During the week of the operation against Alfonso Cano alias, he had been warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for Cauca in a Palmira helicopter.
He knew that he had to identify two bodies and that one of them was suspected of being the man who led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was asked to carry the card with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the scene of the body, he did not recognize it by his physical appearance, because it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He didn't have a beard, he was dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much more leaner.
But prints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian wolf, an encre, a kidnapper and a lantern, Eliaszar compared the fingerprints of the body to those of the map.
His eye did not deceive him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
The same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was responsible who confirmed to the Minister of Defence Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, he was the Supreme Chief of the Farc.
Looking for the print
For a doctyloscopist from Sijín de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos gave to Elias González, in a press conference for the operation against Cano, is very significant.
A lot of people didn't know our job.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate science, without error, which can be crucial in the resolution of crimes.
Apart from identifying corpses, dactyloscopicists support investigations into crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many offenders have false identity cards or no documents.
We take their fingerprints and searches in the database.
The researcher reported that in a flight case he had to remove a part of the wall from a house, because in this place the thief had supported his hand to get out a chest full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces for fingerprinting, but in this case we have been able to get the whole handprint and identify the offender who had participated in various flights," he recalls.
The fingerprints may also remove or confirm suspects in cases of homicide.
Recently, we found a dead man with bottles of drink around him.
Through the investigation, it was determined that a parent could be suspected of the crime and indeed a print on the bottle coincided.
Even if it doesn't guarantee he's the killer, it's the one on the scene of the crime.
A ICT Dactyloscopicist explained that "digital fingerprints of objects with chemical or physical reagents" were extracted.
When they appear, a receiver or a band is used to pick them up.
Later, the prints are sent to Asif, the trigger database, or the National Civil Registry.
"The problem is that there are still a lot of paperless Colombians," said the ITC expert.
He explained that everything is not how to show in the CSI television program.
Since everything that shines is not gold, everything we touch does not necessarily become a print.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is achieved.
