Discouragement?
“No,” says Eric Blanchet, Director General of Adapt, “the association that organizes the week for the employment of persons with disabilities.”
" The progress made for 15 years has been considerable. "
" At that time, the rate of unemployment was not two but three times higher."
" However, there is still a great deal to be done."
It must be said that for the disabled, obstacles remain many before access to employment.
Rather, they are older: 37% have more than 50 years (17% on average).
They have a low qualification level: 80% do not have the pool and of the 2.3 million higher education students, only 10,000 are disabled.
Finally, long-term unemployment is very widespread: 53% for the disabled, compared with 38% on average.
In short, so many criteria that make it particularly difficult to return to employment, and that are "the node of the problem", according to Christian Grapin, Director General of Tremplin, an association established in 1992 to help companies recruit disabled workers.
That's for the target brakes.
It remains the non- so-called mentalities that evolve, certainly, but too slowly.
A study conducted in April by the IMS-Enterprise Association for the City indicated that the managers interviewed had " a low level of knowledge of disability " with " overrepresentation of wheelchair, mental or intellectual disabilities " .
As a result, private enterprises with more than 20 employees are still far from reaching the employment target of 6% of workers with disabilities, as set out in a... 1987 Act.
The last known figures, dating from 2008, show a 2.6% ratio.
"We are now around 3%," says Pierre Blanc, Director General of Agefiph, the agency responsible for collecting the contributions of companies that do not comply with this law.
Evidence: the number of " taxed " institutions, like the amounts paid, decreased between 2007 and 2011, from 59,000 to 46,000 structures (and from 606 to 480 million euros).
" The 2005 Act, which increased contributions, created strong pressure on businesses," explains Pierre Blanc. "
" But this improvement also translates a real awareness, especially in large groups."
According to the Ministry of Employment, only 59 per cent of the 20 to 49 employees in employment employ persons with disabilities, compared with 82 per cent of the 100 to 199 employees.
